Just for your information, below is the commands I used to merge the PR as a committer:

The pull request ID is 1458 for this one, and I assume your github account is liuyutw
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
git clone https://github.com/apache/trafodion 
git remote add apache https://LiuYuTW@git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf/trafodion.git

git fetch apache
git checkout -b mrg_1458 origin/master

git fetch origin +refs/pull/1458/head

git merge --no-ff -m "[TRAFODION-2973] Add syntax and examples of *[LAST N] (SELECT Statement)* in *Trafodion SQL Reference Manual  " FETCH_HEAD

below two commands is just for checking the correctness, you can ignore them:
git log apache/master..HEAD
git diff apache/master HEAD

git push apache HEAD:default

@CoderSong2015 no, I think the best fix is to fix in trafci to catch the WARNING, since in this case, SQL should already return warning. sqlci works correct, but trafci not report WARNING.
If the reporter think ERROR is required, you should change the code I listed above to ERROR instead of WARNING. There are several places in that method, some return ERROR, some return WARNING. So I think you may need to do some debug to check where to change.
I didn't do any debug, so just some suggestions. 
And I recommend to change trafci to return warning in this case, but I don't see what is the real ANSI definition here.
